  <static seed="273" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicMath/FractionApplication/FractionSubtractionWordProblems20.pg">
    <statement><p>Perlia is participating in a running event. In the first hour, she completed <m>{{\frac{3}{8}}}</m> of the total distance. After another hour, in total she had completed <m>{{\frac{13}{24}}}</m> of the total distance.</p>
<p>What fraction of the total distance did Perlia complete during the second hour?</p>
<p>Perlia completed <fillin characters="10" name="AnSwEr0001"/> of the distance during the second hour.</p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>{\frac{1}{6}}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>This is a subtraction problem.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ 
\begin{aligned}[t]
   {{\frac{13}{24}}} - {{\frac{3}{8}}} 
      \amp = \frac{13}{24}-\frac{3 \cdot 3}{8 \cdot 3} \\
      \amp = \frac{13}{24} - \frac{9}{24} \\
      \amp = \frac{13-9}{24} \\
      \amp = \frac{4}{24} \\
      \amp = {{\frac{1}{6}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>Perlia completed <m>{{\frac{1}{6}}}</m> of the distance during the second hour.</p>
</solution>
